[{"id":40374,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>500</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>250</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>250</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>500</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></msub><mo>-</mo></math>Power of source</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mfrac><mi>hc</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#955;</mi></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></math>&nbsp;=&nbsp; no. of photons emitted/s</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>&#8733;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#955;</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>500</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (03 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40331,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>92</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">W</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">W</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">W</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>06</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">W</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The radiation pressure in case of complete absorption is given by,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>I</mi><mi>c</mi></mfrac></math>.</p><p>Therefore, the force will be,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>I</mi><mi>c</mi></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>A</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>I</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>F</mi><mi>c</mi></mrow><mi>A</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>I</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>36</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>600</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">W</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>I</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>06</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">W</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40303,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["$\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{B}}=\\hat{k} \\frac{40}{\\mathrm{C}} \\cos \\omega(\\mathrm{t}-z / \\mathrm{c})$","$\\vec{B}=\\hat{j} 40 \\cos \\omega(t-z / c)$","$\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{B}}=\\hat{i} \\frac{40}{\\mathrm{C}} \\cos \\omega(\\mathrm{t}-z / \\mathrm{c})$","$\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{B}}=\\hat{j} \\frac{40}{\\mathrm{C}} \\cos \\omega(\\mathrm{t}-z / \\mathrm{c})$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{E}}=\\hat{\\mathrm{i}} 40 \\cos \\omega\\left(\\mathrm{t}-\\frac{\\mathrm{z}}{\\mathrm{c}}\\right)$\n$\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{E}}$ is along $+\\mathrm{x}$ direction\n$\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{v}}$ is along $+\\mathrm{z}$ direction\nSo direction of $\\vec{B}$ will be along +y and magnitude of $B$ will be $\\frac{E}{c}$\nSo answer is $\\frac{40}{c} \\cos \\omega\\left(t-\\frac{z}{c}\\right) \\hat{j}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (04 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40419,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["X-ray region","Ultra violet region","Infrared region","Visible region"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\mathrm{E}=\\frac{\\mathrm{hc}}{\\lambda} \\Rightarrow \\lambda=\\frac{\\mathrm{hc}}{\\mathrm{E}}$\n$\\Rightarrow \\lambda=\\frac{6.6 \\times 10^{-34} \\times 3 \\times 10^8}{11 \\times 1000 \\times 1.6 \\times 10^{-19}}$\n$=12.4 Å$\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/yKtvG7cFMj51zKR5Z4qU9F-Z-tk8PUWjWXSbG67Cigc.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\nwavelength range of visible region is $4000 Å$ to $7800 Å$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":40336,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>18</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>54</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>54</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>18</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mi>y</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>540</mn><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Here, peak value of electric field,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>540</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Using relation between magnetic and electric field,&nbsp;</p><p>Peak value of magnetic field is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>c</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>540</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40272,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["$0.58$","$0.67$","$0.82$","$0.75$"],"answer":1,"solution":"The displacement current $I_d$ between the plates of a capacitor is given by the formula:<br><br>$I_d = C \\dfrac{dV}{dt}$<br><br>Substituting the given values of displacement current and capacitance:<br><br>$4.0 = 6 \\times 10^{-6} \\times \\dfrac{dV}{dt}$<br><br>$\\dfrac{dV}{dt} = \\dfrac{4.0}{6 \\times 10^{-6}}$<br><br>$\\dfrac{dV}{dt} = \\dfrac{2}{3} \\times 10^6 \\approx 0.67 \\times 10^6$ V/s<br><br>Comparing this with the given rate of change of potential difference $\\alpha \\times 10^6$ V/s, we get $\\alpha = 0.67$.<br><br>Answer: $0.67$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (05 April Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40371,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>c</mi></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mover><mi>x</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mover><mi>y</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>c</mi></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mover><mi>x</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mover><mi>y</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>c</mi></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mover><mi>x</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>-</mo><mover><mi>y</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>c</mi></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mover><mi>x</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>-</mo><mover><mi>y</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>z</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"As in electromagnetic&nbsp; wave electric field is always perpendicular to the magnetic field and both the fields oscillates perpendicularly to the direction pf propagation so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#215;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#8214;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></math>&nbsp;","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (04 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40410,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>73</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>48</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/P_35_Ans_Correction.jpg\" style=\"width: 122px; height: 126px;\" /><br /><br />For a point source of power = P, then intensity at a point at a separation x from the source is,&nbsp;<math><mi>I</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>w</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msup><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math><math><mo>&#8757;</mo></math>&nbsp;The average intensity of E.M. wave is given by,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>c</mi><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msubsup><mi>E</mi><mi>o</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>c</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8757;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><msub><mi>&#949;</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>9</mn></msup><mo>,</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0.1</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">W</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0.1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>9</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>2.45</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (04 Apr)","image":null},{"id":40338,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mi>y</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mover><mrow><mi>j</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mi>z</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mover><mi>k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math></p>","<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mi>y</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mover><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>j</mi></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mi>z</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup><mi>sin</mi><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mover><mi>k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math></p>","<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mi>y</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup><mi>sin</mi><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mover><mi>j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mi>z</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mover><mi>k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math></p>","<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mi>y</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup><mi>sin</mi><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mover><mi>j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>B</mi><mi>z</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>4</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mover><mi>k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math></p>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Using the relation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></math>, where,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp;is speed of light in vacuum.</p><p>After analysing each option, we get option&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>&nbsp;is the correct option</p><p>as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mover><mi>E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>60</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40369,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>36</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>11</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mn>36</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>11</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mn>36</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>11</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mn>36</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>11</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mfrac></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&#215;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>36</mn></math></p><p>As the light is propagating in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> direction.</p><p>&amp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#215;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>|</mo><mo>|</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></math> should be in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math> direction.</p><p>So electric field <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>sin</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#183;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>36</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>11</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (06 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40375,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>sin</mi><mo>[</mo><mn>200</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>ct</mi><mo>)</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup><mi>sin</mi><mo>[</mo><mn>200</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>ct</mi><mo>)</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mi>sin</mi><mo>[</mo><mn>200</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>ct</mi><mo>)</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>sin</mi><mo>[</mo><mn>200</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>ct</mi><mo>)</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">0</mn></msub><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">=</mo><mi>c</mi><msub><mi>B</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">0</mn></msub></math></em></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#8756;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">E</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#8594;</mo></mover><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#215;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">B</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#8594;</mo></mover><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#8214;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">C</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#8594;</mo></mover><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#8658;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">k</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">^</mo></mover><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#215;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">i</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">^</mo></mover><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">=</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">j</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">^</mo></mover></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mi>sin</mi><mo>[</mo><mn>200</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>ct</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>)</mo><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>sin</mi><mo>[</mo><mn>200</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>ct</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>]</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>)</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (03 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40333,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>10</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mi>y</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>900</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#969;</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><mi>c</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>900</mn></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4908a3d2-9c62-4497-b650-2e3c0c09bf47-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 132px;\" /></p><p>Electric field and electric force are related as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>E</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></p><p>Magnetic force of a moving charge is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi><mi>v</mi><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></p><p>Thus, the ratio&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>E</mi></msub><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mrow><mi>v</mi><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Using relation between magnetic and electric field, we have</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>E</mi></msub><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>B</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mi>v</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>7</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40295,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$i_d=i_c$\n$\\therefore$ Total displacement current $=6 \\mathrm{~A}$\nThrough $A_0$\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& i=\\left(\\frac{A_0}{A}\\right) 6 \\\\\n& =\\frac{3.2}{16} \\times 6=1.2 \\mathrm{~A}=1200 \\mathrm{~mA}\n\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (22 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40271,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["$\\dfrac{I_o}{4}$","$I_o$","$\\dfrac{I_o}{\\sqrt{2}}$","$\\dfrac{I_o}{2}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"For a point light source, the intensity of electromagnetic waves at a distance $r$ is given by $I = \\dfrac{P}{4\\pi r^2}$, where $P$ is the power of the source.<br><br>Since the detector is moved to a new location on the same spherical surface, the distance from the source remains $L$.<br><br>The emission from a point source is isotropic, meaning the intensity depends only on the radial distance from the source and is independent of the angular position.<br><br>Therefore, the intensity at the new location remains unchanged, which is $I_o$.<br><br>Answer: $I_o$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (06 April Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40361,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>24</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>24</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Hz</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>EM</mi></math> wave is travelling towards <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">z</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>E</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#215;</mo><mover><mi>C</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">z</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>24</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (16 Mar Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40427,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["wavelength is doubled and the frequency remains unchanged","wavelength is doubled and frequency becomes half","wavelength is halved and frequency remains unchanged","wavelength and frequency both remain unchanged."],"answer":2,"solution":"Refractive index, $\\mu=\\sqrt{\\frac{\\varepsilon}{\\varepsilon_0}}=2$\nSpeed and wavelength of wave will becomes half, the frequency remaining unchanged (frequency of a wave depends on the source as due to refraction, it is assumed that the energy is conserved. hv remains the same)","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2004","image":null},{"id":40420,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>V</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>V</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>V</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>V</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>E</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup></math><br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mo>=&#160;</mo> <mtext>6 V/m</mtext> </mrow> </math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (07 Apr)","image":null},{"id":40335,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>Vm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> along <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>Vm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> along <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math>-axis","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>Vm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> along <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math>-axis","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>Vm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> along&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math>-axis"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The ratio of electric field amplitude to the magnetic field amplitude of an electromagnetic wave is equal to the speed of light in the medium. Therefore,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi><msub><mi>B</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>E</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>According to the given equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>B</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>11</mn></msup><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math>&nbsp;the wave travels in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;direction. As electric field and magnetic field vibrate perpendicular to the velocity of light, electric field can not be along&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;axis.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40389,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["<math><mi> </mi><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi></math> along z-direction","<math><mi> </mi><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math>  along y-direction","<math><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math>  along z-direction","<math><mi> </mi><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math>  along x-direction"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math>  <br/><math><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>×</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo></mover></math> is along <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></math> -direction <br/><math><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>×</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></math>  <br/><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>  <br/><math><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo></mover></math> is along <math><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></math>  <br/><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></msup><mtext> </mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math> along <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">z</mi></math> -direction","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40291,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["$\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{E}}=\\left(\\frac{1}{2} \\hat{i}-\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\hat{j}\\right) 30 \\mathrm{c} \\sin \\left[\\omega\\left(\\mathrm{t}-\\frac{z}{\\mathrm{c}}\\right)\\right]$","$\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{E}}=\\left(\\frac{3}{4} \\hat{i}+\\frac{1}{4} \\hat{j}\\right) 30 \\mathrm{c} \\cos \\left[\\omega\\left(\\mathrm{t}-\\frac{z}{\\mathrm{c}}\\right)\\right]$","$\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{E}}=\\left(\\frac{1}{2} \\hat{i}+\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\hat{j}\\right) 30 \\mathrm{c} \\sin \\left[\\omega\\left(\\mathrm{t}+\\frac{z}{\\mathrm{c}}\\right)\\right]$","$\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{E}}=\\left(\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\hat{i}-\\frac{1}{2} \\hat{j}\\right) 30 \\mathrm{c} \\sin \\left[\\omega\\left(\\mathrm{t}+\\frac{z}{\\mathrm{c}}\\right)\\right]$"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{B}}=\\left(\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}+\\frac{1}{2} \\hat{\\mathrm{j}}\\right) 30 \\sin \\left[\\omega\\left(\\mathrm{t}-\\frac{\\mathrm{z}}{\\mathrm{c}}\\right)\\right] \\\\\n& \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{E}}=\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{B}} \\times \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{c}} \\text { and } \\mathrm{E}=\\mathrm{B}_0 \\mathrm{c}\n\\end{aligned}$\n\nHere $\\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{E}}\\left(\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}(-\\hat{\\mathrm{j}})+\\frac{1}{2} \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}\\right)$\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\mathrm{E}_0=30 \\mathrm{c} \\\\\n& \\overrightarrow{\\mathrm{E}}=\\left(\\frac{1}{2} \\hat{\\mathrm{i}}-\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\hat{\\mathrm{j}}\\right) 30 \\mathrm{c} \\sin \\left[\\omega\\left(\\mathrm{t}-\\frac{\\mathrm{z}}{\\mathrm{c}}\\right)\\right]\n\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (28 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40311,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Electromagnetic Waves","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>35</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">W</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>53</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">W</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>26</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">W</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>106</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">W</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>The magnitude of the electric field component of the electromagnetic wave is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>200</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>The formula to calculate the intensity of the electromagnetic wave is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>ε</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">0</mn></msub><mi>c</mi><msubsup><mi>E</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">0</mn><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">2</mn></msubsup><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>From equation (1), it follows that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mi>I</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>85</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup><mo>×</mo><msup><mfenced><mn>200</mn></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">W</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</m